HEADWORD: Materiality
<hw>Ma*te`ri*al"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>mat⟦eacute⟧rialit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of being material; material
existence; corporeity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Importance; <as>as, the <ex>materiality</ex> of
facts</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Materialization</ent>⟦br⟧
